# Design implementation

## Analyze provided UI designs (images or descriptions).

## Detect repeating patterns such as:
   - buttons
   - inputs
   - cards
   - spacing
   - typography
   - colors

## When patterns repeat:
   - Extract them into reusable React components
   - Use clean and scalable structure

## Always:
   - Use TypeScript
   - Use functional React components
   - Use Tailwind CSS
   - Follow consistent naming

## Component rules:
   - If same UI appears 2+ times → create component
   - Components must be reusable and configurable (props)
   - Avoid duplication

## Design system rules:
   - Define color variables if reused
   - Define spacing scale
   - Define button variants (primary, secondary, etc.)

## Output structure:
  - components/ui
  - components/common
  - pages

## When image is provided:
   - First describe detected UI patterns
   - Then propose component structure
   - Then generate code

## Always explain your decisions briefly.

## Be consistent with previous outputs.